"title": "4921: day",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4921",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A period of 24 hours or, as distinct from night, the period of daylight. The term may also be used more generally to refer to a point in time. Daylight is used figuratively to describe the illumination afforded to believers, who are urged to use the opportunities it presents and to avoid the evil usually associated with darkness.</p>\n<h2>Day and daylight</h2>\n<h3>Day as a period of 24 hours</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:8\">GEN 1:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:19\">MAT 20:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:43\">JHN 4:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:6\">JHN 11:6</a></p>\n<h3>Day as the period of daylight</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:5\">GEN 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:14-Gen1:18\">GEN 1:14–1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:22\">GEN 8:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:16\">PSA 74:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:20\">JER 33:20</a></p>\n<h2>Daylight gives opportunity for activity</h2>\n<h3>A time for human endeavour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:9-John11:10\">JHN 11:9–11:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:12-Josh10:13\">JOS 10:12–10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:29\">ACT 27:29</a></p>\n<h3>A time of spiritual opportunity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4-John9:5\">JHN 9:4–9:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:35-John12:36\">JHN 12:35–12:36</a></p>\n<h2>Daylight allows things to be seen</h2>\n<h3>Daylight activities are seen by all</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:11-2Sam12:12\">2SA 12:11–12:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:3-Ezek12:4\">EZK 12:3–12:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:27\">MAT 10:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:3\">LUK 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those avoiding daylight</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:27\">JDG 6:27</a> <em>Gideon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:2\">JHN 3:2</a> <em>Nicodemus</em></p>\n<h3>Daylight activities should be decent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:12-Rom13:13\">ROM 13:12–13:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8-Eph5:14\">EPH 5:8–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:5-1Thess5:8\">1TH 5:5–5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:13\">2PE 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>Six working days ordained</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:11\">EXO 20:8–20:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12-Deut5:15\">DEU 5:12–5:15</a></p>\n<h2>Particular days of the week</h2>\n<h3>The Sabbath (Saturday)</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:10\">EXO 20:8–20:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12-Deut5:15\">DEU 5:12–5:15</a> <em>The Sabbath was reckoned from sunset on Friday to sunset on Saturday.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:16\">LUK 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:16\">COL 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:4\">HEB 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>The Day of Preparation for the Sabbath (Friday)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:42\">MRK 15:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:54\">LUK 23:54</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:31\">JHN 19:31</a></p>\n<h3>The first day of the week (Sunday)</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:7\">ACT 20:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:2\">MRK 16:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1\">LUK 24:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:1\">JHN 20:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:9\">MRK 16:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:2\">1CO 16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:10\">REV 1:10</a></p>\n<h2>Festival days</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:5-Lev23:6\">LEV 23:5–23:6</a> <em>Passover and Unleavened Bread</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:27-Lev23:28\">LEV 23:27–23:28</a> <em>the Day of Atonement</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:34-Lev23:36\">LEV 23:34–23:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37\">JHN 7:37</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:26\">NUM 28:26</a> <em>the day of firstfruits</em></p>\n<h2>Day as a point in time</h2>\n<h3>The day of salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:2\">2CO 6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:9\">ISA 25:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:8\">ISA 49:8</a></p>\n<h3>God sends the day of disaster</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:35\">DEU 32:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:18\">JER 17:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:2\">JER 51:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:19\">MRK 13:19</a></p>\n<h3>God helps on the day of distress</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:7\">PSA 86:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:3\">GEN 35:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:19\">2SA 22:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:18\">PSA 18:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:3-2Kgs19:4\">2KI 19:3–19:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:3-Isa37:4\">ISA 37:3–37:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:13\">PSA 94:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:17\">JER 17:17</a></p>\n<h2>The final days of time</h2>\n<h3>The last days</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17-Acts2:18\">ACT 2:17–2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28-Joel2:29\">JOL 2:28–2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2\">ISA 2:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1\">MIC 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:5\">HOS 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1\">1TI 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1\">2TI 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2\">HEB 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:20\">1PE 1:20</a></p>\n<h3>The day of the LORD</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9-Isa13:11\">ISA 13:9–13:11</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:7-Jer30:9\">JER 30:7–30:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:16-Zeph3:17\">ZEP 3:16–3:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:6\">PHP 1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:1-Joel2:2\">JOL 2:1–2:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:15\">OBA 1:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:14-Zeph1:15\">ZEP 1:14–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:2\">1TH 5:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10\">2PE 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>The last day</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:39-John6:40\">JHN 6:39–6:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:24\">JHN 11:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:48\">JHN 12:48</a></p>\n<h2>References to specific periods of days at the end of history</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:11-Dan12:12\">DAN 12:11–12:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:3\">REV 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:6\">REV 12:6</a></p>\n<h2>God's different perception of time</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:8\">2PE 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:4\">PSA 90:4</a></p>",
